article.description: Jeremy Miller scored 15 points and grabbed a career-high 11 rebounds and Northeastern rolled to an 88-56 victory over Delaware on Thursday night.
article.headline: Northeastern cruises to 88-56 victory over Delaware
article.linkText: Northeastern cruises to 88-56 victory over Delaware
article.story: BOSTON -- Jeremy Miller scored 15 points and grabbed a career-high 11 rebounds and Northeastern rolled to an 88-56 victory over Delaware on Thursday night. The Huskies (11-5, 3-0 Colonial Athletic Conference) have won three consecutive games and are off to their best start since the 2008-09 season. Quincy Ford had 13 points, and Devon Begley chipped in nine points with five assists for Northeastern. Kory Holden scored 14 points with four 3-pointers and six assists to lead Delaware (5-9, 0-3), which has lost six straight. The Huskies jumped out on a 21-4 run six minutes into the game and had a double-digit lead the rest of the way. Miller scored six points and Ford had five during the span. Caleb Donnelly made back-to-back 3s to stretch the Huskies' lead to 64-33 with 13 minutes left. Donnelly finished with nine points.
